bd5ca58dc600ed09be1","event_uuid":"dcd2777c-6c7a-454f-9987-649b0fdd5a91","position":{"commit_sha":"116101410bdcecaf14e7fcdcda374ffee521bee3","position":"1784432983472721001-dcd2777c-6c7a-454f-9987-649b0fdd5a91"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"34cdd114972323bc8c4c57004eccd09b7ac5fd5a6d006e37f035510df41f08b9","event_uuid":"20e287e0-7e2f-421b-87e8-566997f2430f","position":{"commit_sha":"116101410bdcecaf14e7fcdcda374ffee521bee3","position":"1784432983712391001-20e287e0-7e2f-421b-87e8-566997f2430f"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"83154d8892c298eecffcb3f6811d031d6bbaeb45646043c59d1648e0e0c0dbef","event_uuid":"723a8b48-d489-4095-adc5-9cd1e881d1f8","position":{"commit_sha":"f8e1d9df0ef22ac618c74bd62851e7e8df216704","position":"1784433391639128674-723a8b48-d489-4095-adc5-9cd1e881d1f8"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"}],"bridge_alerts":[],"claim_harness":"claude-code_2-1-214_agent","claim_remote_session":null,"claimed_session":"6e3fbad8-702f-4987-ad70-cc88122eea43","comments":[],"created_at":1784416828704053001,"creation_channel":"cli","deps":[],"description":"## What\nCapture env/integration-diagnosis passively by writing an additive `verdict=\"ERROR\"` gate-sidecar record (with an `error{cause,evidence_ref}` object) on the gates' infrastructure-exception path, so a diagnosis interval starts (ERROR) and ends (next PASS) is recorded by gate code, never by agent self-report.\n\n## Current behavior (verified against the code — the plan MUST fit this)\nThe three gates handle an infra exception (`LLMUnavailableError`) **asymmetrically**, and this ticket does NOT change that:\n- `produce_plan_review_verdict` (gate_dispatch.py:110) and `produce_code_review_verdict` (:512) **catch** `LLMUnavailableError` and **return a degraded INDETERMINATE** verdict (`_degraded_plan_review_verdict` :395 / `_degraded_code_review_verdict` :456) — a soft-degrade contract that must be preserved.\n- `produce_completion_verdict` (:634) does **not** catch it — the exception **propagates** and the close gate fail-closes.\n- `plan_review/sidecar.build_payload` writes schema `plan_review_result_v2` and does NOT reconcile the verdict; `completion_sidecar.build_payload` routes through `reconcile_verdict` (completion.py:214) which **coerces any non-PASS to FAIL** — so a naive `verdict=\"ERROR\"` on the completion payload would be flattened to FAIL.\n- Readers are schema-guarded: `latest_review_result`/`all_review_results` accept only `plan_review_result_v1|v2`; `latest_fail_verdict`/`latest_pass_record` accept only `completion_verifier_fail_v1`/`pass_v1`. An unrecognized schema is silently skipped.\n\n## Files & approach\n- `src/rebar/llm/workflow/gate_dispatch.py` — classify an infra exception (provider 5xx/connection/tooling) at each existing `except LLMUnavailableError` site, and **additively** write an ERROR sidecar record there, **preserving the existing per-gate outcome**:\n  - plan-review + code-review infra sites: emit the ERROR record, then `return` the existing degraded INDETERMINATE verdict (write-then-degrade — the soft-degrade contract is unchanged).\n  - completion infra site: wrap preflight (:651) so it emits the ERROR record then **re-raises** (write-then-reraise — the fail-closed contract is unchanged).\n  - A domain BLOCK/FAIL (non-infra) writes **no** ERROR record.\n- **Dedicated schema tag `gate_error_v1`** (NOT a reuse of the verdict schemas) with a small dedicated payload builder `build_error_payload(gate, cause, evidence_ref)` → `{schema:\"gate_error_v1\", verdict:\"ERROR\", gate:<plan_review|code_review|completion>, error:{cause,evidence_ref}}`. Because it is a separate builder it **never routes through `reconcile_verdict`**, so the `ERROR` verdict survives (is not coerced to FAIL). Written on the **existing** event types — `REVIEW_RESULT` (plan/code-review) and `COMPLETION_VERDICT` (completion) — so **no new event type** is introduced (both are already non-replay + in the write allow-list).\n- `src/rebar/llm/plan_review/sidecar.py`, `src/rebar/llm/completion_sidecar.py` — add the `build_error_payload` helper + an `emit_error(...)` path (default-absent). The existing verdict readers are **left unchanged**: their schema guards naturally skip `gate_error_v1`, so no existing reader ever surfaces an ERROR record unexpectedly. The metrics gate-sidecar reader (ticket 3c07) is the consumer that reads `gate_error_v1`.\n- `tests/unit/workflow/test_gate_error_sidecar.py` — new.\n\n## Back-compat\nPurely additive: older readers ignore `gate_error_v1`; no verdict-builder or reconcile path changes; back-out = stop emitting the ERROR record. Only gate-encountered infra failures are captured — a deliberate, stated scope limit (shell/CI toil outside a gate stays out of scope). Stamped by gate code on a real failure, so the self-report reliability problem does not apply.\n\n## Tests\n- Unit: a stubbed plan-review run raising `LLMUnavailableError` writes a `REVIEW_RESULT` record with `schema=\"gate_error_v1\"`, `verdict=\"ERROR\"`, non-empty `error.cause`, AND the gate still returns INDETERMINATE (degrade preserved). A domain BLOCK writes no ERROR record. The completion infra path writes the ERROR record then re-raises. Existing `latest_review_result`/`latest_fail_verdict` do not surface the ERROR record.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `tests/unit/workflow/test_gate_error_sidecar.py` passes: injecting an infra exception at a gate yields a persisted `gate_error_v1` record with `jq -e '.verdict==\"ERROR\"'` and non-empty `error.cause`.\n- [ ] the gate's pre-existing outcome is preserved on the infra path — plan-review/code-review still return INDETERMINATE, and the completion path still propagates the exception — asserted by the test.\n- [ ] a domain BLOCK/FAIL produces no `gate_error_v1` record — unit test asserts absence.\n- [ ] existing verdict readers (`latest_review_result`, `latest_fail_verdict`) never return the ERROR record — unit test asserts the schema guard skips it (so the ERROR verdict is not coerced to FAIL and does not pollute verdict reads).","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[{"path":"src/rebar/llm/workflow/gate_dispatch.py","reason":"ERROR on infra exception"},{"path":"src/rebar/llm/plan_review/sidecar.py","reason":"ERROR verdict"},{"path":"src/rebar/llm/completion_sidecar.py","reason":"ERROR verdict"}],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[["parent","86ac-086a-20ad-4327"]],"parent_id":"86ac-086a-20ad-4327","parent_status_uuid":"dcd2777c-6c7a-454f-9987-649b0fdd5a91","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":2,"reverts":[],"status":"in_progress","tags":["metrics","schema"],"ticket_id":"8bc5-9c76-95f3-465e","ticket_type":"task","title":"Gate ERROR outcome on the infra-exception path (env-diagnosis start)","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["cbdafdc2-1959-40b3-9a45-76eb5d8f3f8f","6f3258ee-cfb2-45d6-b3fd-d145c786ba14","55b65627-f303-40cf-8806-fd89b69b1044","6baae32a-84f1-4308-adb7-e418ed41455c","dcd2777c-6c7a-454f-9987-649b0fdd5a91","20e287e0-7e2f-421b-87e8-566997f2430f","723a8b48-d489-4095-adc5-9cd1e881d1f8"]},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"SNAPSHOT","timestamp":1784433391639128675,"uuid":"12ac516e-f634-46b8-a766-67a33306d256"}